# Agentic AI Desktop

Desktop demo app for the Agentic AI system.
Built with Electron — runs on Windows and Mac.

---

## Prerequisites

- Node.js 18+
- npm

---

## Run locally (development)

```bash
npm install
npm start
```

This opens the app immediately without building an installer.
Requires an internet connection — the app calls the Vercel API.

---

## Build installers

### Windows (.exe installer)
Run this on a Windows machine:
```bash
npm install
npm run build:win
```
Output: `dist/Agentic AI Setup 1.0.0.exe`

### Mac (.dmg installer)
Run this on a Mac:
```bash
npm install
npm run build:mac
```
Output: `dist/Agentic AI-1.0.0.dmg`

---

## Important

- The app requires an active internet connection
- It calls `https://ai-support-sprint.vercel.app/api/demo`
- If the Vercel project URL changes, update `API_URL` in `renderer/index.html`

---

## Icons

Before building installers, add proper icon files:
- `assets/icon.ico` — Windows (256x256 .ico file)
- `assets/icon.icns` — Mac (.icns file)
- `assets/icon.png` — 512x512 PNG (used as fallback)

You can generate these from a single PNG at https://cloudconvert.com
